reviewText: While we're going camping, we're going to have some songs and fun and dancing, and excitement, and all the rest.This video ranks high up there with the "live action" ones, what with the Sing Along gang joining in with Mickey, Minnie, Goofy, Chip and Dale, and the others in a fun fest which brings you on a tour of many of the sights of Discovery Island and River Country.  Donald Duck is there camping out, as is Goofy, and the sight of him water skiing is worth the price of the video.  (He's actually quite good!!!)Then there are the songs - many from years before, such as "The Caissons Go Marching Along," "Don't Fence Me In," "Mountain Greenery," and when the dancers do "Turkey in the Straw," it's a real hoot, and our two twin girls want to get up and dance and dance and dance....A terrific addition to any collection!!!

reviewText: This was the first sing-along DVD we ever bought & everyone in my family loves it, from my mom who babysits, to my 2 year old who knows all the songs as well as everyone else!  One or 2 of the kids in the video over-act a little, but the movie is totally worth buying.  Some of the songs everyone knows from the very start, while others are vaugly familiar & you'll learn them quickly---from If You're Happy and You Know It to John Denver's Take Me Home (Country road).  It's fast-paced enough to hold the interest of the younger ones, with enough viewing pleasure to entertain the older ones.
